{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_014cyDrEcJ3CMJVmwrJwzF1u","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me analyze the failure patterns from the digest and write the feedback.md file.\n\nLooking at the failures:\n\n1. **OCR corruption - digit/letter substitution causing empty extraction**:\n   - \"Braised Cod with White Wine\": title is \"Bra1sed Cod w1th Wh1te W1ne\" → extracted empty\n   - \"Roasted Beet and Walnut Dip\": title is \"Roasted Beet and Walnut D1p\" → extracted empty\n   - \"Piernik z Śliwkami\": title is \"P1ern1k z Śliwkami\" → extracted a line from the body\n   - \"Drożdże Sernik\": title is \"Drożdże Sern1k\" → extracted a line from the body\n\n2. **OCR corruption causing wrong extraction (partial match)**:\n   - \"Sole with Brown Butter and Capers\": title is \"S01e with Brown Butter and Capers\" → extracted \"S0ie with Brown Butter and Capers\" (slightly wrong normalization)\n\n3. **Title not at top / multi-recipe document**:\n   - \"Mushroom Risotto\": the title isn't at the start; the document starts with instructions and has \"CARPACCIO DI PESCE\" appearing first → extracted that other title instead\n\n4. **Title in metadata header / not first prominent text**:\n   - \"Ogórkowa Zupa\": document starts with \"Lato | Zupy | DLA 4 OSÓB | ...\" then \"OGÓRKOWA ZUPA\" → extracted empty\n\n5. **OCR corruption with dotless i and garbage tokens**:\n   - \"Kopytka z Pieczarkami Leśnymi\": \"KoPyTka z P¡eczarkami Leśnymi\" → extracted body text \"Ugotuj ziemniaky. (38)\"\n   - \"Żurek Krakowski\": starts correctly but has garbage tokens → extracted \"Xxyyzz salt and pepper\"\n\nNow I'm grouping these patterns more systematically to understand where the extraction is failing.\n\nWhen OCR corrupts the title with digit-for-letter substitutions like \"Bra1sed Cod w1th Wh1te W1ne\" or \"Roasted Beet and Walnut D1p\", the extractor returns nothing entirely. But with other corrupted titles like \"Drożdże Sern1k\" or \"P1ern1k z Śliwkami\", it's pulling the wrong line from the recipe body instead—usually something from the serving instructions at the end. This suggests the extractor might be rejecting certain noise patterns outright while attempting to recover from others, sometimes landing on completely unrelated text. I'm seeing several distinct failure patterns here. When titles aren't at the document start or are preceded by metadata lines, the extractor gets thrown off and either picks the wrong section or returns nothing. Mixed-case text with special characters like dotless i's also confuses the system into grabbing body text instead of the actual title. There's also the case where documents are mis-scanned or contain multiple recipes, so the extractor latches onto whatever header it finds rather than the intended title.\n\nFor the Sole with Brown Butter and Capers example, the extractor is doing partial OCR correction—it fixes some character errors but not others, getting close but not quite right. Since all nine failures are from generated files, I should make note of that in the feedback.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":3,"cache_creation_input_tokens":11612,"cache_read_input_tokens":10352,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":11612},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"77635614-824e-4e67-b0ab-798a41cb8262","uuid":"977e3b91-df6c-418d-a8a3-1864f3aa720b"}
